RACE.RACE_TEXT: GRANTS PASS RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 65. Claiming Purse 6500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500 (Races at OR Fairs or WA Class C Tracks Not Considered in Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SMOKE AND BURN was well placed to the second turn, rallied three wide to the stretch then continued to respond and wore down BOY HOWDY late. BOY HOWDY set the pace under pressure, turned back CAPES HOT ROCKET on the second turn, inched away to the stretch then could not stall the winner. STANLEY RYDER chased the lead to the second turn, made a bid inside to loom boldly into the stretch but could not sustain that bid and went evenly late. HASHTAG BAE stalked the pace to the far turn, was four wide and was giving way in the drive. CAPES HOT ROCKET pressed the pace for three eighths, made a run at BOY HOWDY nearing the second turn while three wide but tired in the final eighth.

ENTRY.NAME: Boy Howdy
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace, met bid 2d turn, inched clear, caught

ENTRY.NAME: Stanley Ryder
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased pace, rail bid, loomed upper stretch, flattened

ENTRY.NAME: Smoke and Burn
ENTRY.COMMENT: never far back, rallied 3wide, steady bid, in time

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GRANTS PASS RACE 3 5F Dirt CR: 73. Allowance Purse 8000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. (Races at OR Fairs or WA Class C Tracks Not Considered in Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LUCINDA RELLA contested the pace to the second turn, saved ground to the stretch then responded to urging to prevail. BABY CHOCOLATE checked off heels and shifted four wide on the first turn, dueled outside the winner to the stretch then was outkicked to the line. GOOD JOB JACKIE broke out, got outrun to the first turn, tracked the leaders two wide but lacked a closing response. SMILING SALSA had no speed, was three then four wide to the stretch and came up empty in the drive. LADY RANGER hustled along early to attend the pace to the second turn then got outkicked and tired.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOB'S SNIPER chased the leader then pushed up on the backstretch to take the lead, edged away to the stretch and held driving. SNICKER'N DAN chased the pace for three eighths then gave way.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Daily Courier S. GRANTS PASS RACE 7 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 87. Stakes Purse 13500. FOR THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. FREE nominations closed Tuesday, August 29 with eleven. Or by supplementary nomination of $150 each by closing time of entries. $200 to pass the entry box. Preference by total earnings in 2022-2023. Field will be limited to ten starters. Three-Year-Olds 124 lbs.; Older 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CODE CHARLIE had the best speed, set all the pace then pushed clear and was never threatened. MR. MISCHIEF broke slow, saved ground to the stretch and was second best. FANTASTIC DAY bobbled at the start, chased the pace, was three wide but could not offer the needed bid. PULPITS POWER had no speed and was not a factor. LIVE A GOOD LIFE pressed the pace for three eighths then weakened. TIZ INDY tracked the pace early but was outkicked after three eighths then gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Mr. Mischief
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke slow, saved ground, late bid 2d

ENTRY.NAME: Code Charlie
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace, pushed clear, never threatened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GRANTS PASS RACE 8 5F Dirt CR: 65. Maiden Special Weight Purse 8000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LET GEORGE DO IT had good speed then was under a hold while the loose horse went by into the backstretch, pushed again to the lead then drew away in final furlong. COLE'S DYNAMITE had no speed, closed the gap while riders were unsure of the loose horse and fallen jockey, got outkicked leaving the furlong pole but saved the place. NEATAPAR tracked the pace early, was under a hold while being careful about the loose horse and fallen rider, stayed closed to the second turn then weakened in the stretch. SMOKENSILVER pressed the winner early, pushed past that one into the backstretch but relinquished the advantage back to LET GEORGE DO IT quickly, got outkicked on the second turn and tired. SENOR AT WAR dwelt at the start and was well back but closed the gap down the backstretch, stayed close for three furlongs but had little left for the stretch run. OUR HY ROLLER broke clean but ducked in sharply at the gap about a hundred yards from the gate and lost his rider. The stewards conducted an inquiry into the accident but made no change to the order.

ENTRY.NAME: Senor At War
ENTRY.COMMENT: dwelt start, closed gap, nothing left

ENTRY.NAME: Our Hy Roller
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke clean, ducked at gap, lost rider

ENTRY.NAME: Smokensilver
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed early, took brief lead, outkicked, tired stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Neatapar
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked pace, 2wide 2d turn, no rally, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Let George Do It
ENTRY.COMMENT: good speed, waited 1st turn, dueled, kicked away, handily

ENTRY.NAME: Cole's Dynamite
ENTRY.COMMENT: no speed, closed gap backstretch, outkicked, saved 2d
